     high = max(max_val - k, nums[i] + k)\n            low = min(min_val + k, nums[i + 1] - k)\n            result = min(result, high - low)\n        \n        return result\n```\n\nThis solution sorts the array first and then iteratively calculates the potential new maximum and minimum values by considering the effect of adding or subtracting `k` at each index. The goal is to minimize the difference between the maximum and minimum values of the modified array.", "estimated_date": 1537660800000}